{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863638938,"sessionID":"ses_286479a04ffe1Yy62joY7hCNz1","part":{"id":"prt_d79b8a3be00101svdtaack61Ye","messageID":"msg_d79b892e50012zCOybY6cLIk4z","sessionID":"ses_286479a04ffe1Yy62joY7hCNz1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f7ba5a44c42f48048cd5109f948cec21","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: PicoD JWT 中间件提供基于 RSA 公钥的 JWT token 验证机制，用于保护 PicoD 的 `/api/*` 端点。该中间件从环境变量加载公钥，验证请求中的 Bearer token，并将验证结果传递给后续处理器。\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n23: │   Router        │────▶│     PicoD       │────▶│   Sandbox       │\n24: │ (JWT Token Gen) │     │  (pkg/picod)    │     │ (Execution Env) │\n25: └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n26:         │                       │\n27:         │                       │\n28:         ▼                       ▼\n29: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────\n30: │  JWTManager     │     │  AuthManager    │\n31: │ (Private Key)   │     │  (Public Key)   │\n32: └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n33: ```\n34: \n35: Router 使用私钥签发 JWT token，PicoD 使用公钥验证 token。密钥通过 Kubernetes Secret 持久化存储。\n36: \n37: ### Component Diagram\n38: \n39: ```\n40: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n41: │                          Server                                  │\n42: │  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │\n43: │  │  Config   │  │ AuthManager  │  │      gin.Engine           │ │\n44: │  │           │  │              │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  │ │\n45: │  │  Port     │  │  publicKey   │  │  │ /health (no auth)   │  │ │\n46: │  │  Workspace│  │  mutex       │──│──│ /api/* (JWT auth)   │  │ │\n47: │  └───────────┘  └──────────────┘  │  └─────────────────────┘  │ │\n48: │                                   │  ┌─────────────────────┐  │ │\n49: │                                   │  │ Handlers            │  │ │\n50: │                                   │  │ - ExecuteHandler    │  │ │\n51: │                                   │  │ - UploadFileHandler │  │ │\n52: │                                   │  │ - ListFilesHandler  │  │ │\n53: │                                   │  │ - DownloadFileHandler│  │ │\n54: │                                   │  └─────────────────────┘  │ │\n55: │                                   └───────────────────────────┘ │\n56: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Request Flow\n60: \n61: ```\n62: Client Request (with Authorization: Bearer <token>)\n63:         │\n64:         ▼\n65: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n66: │ 1. Gin Engine Entry                                             │\n67: │    - Route: /api/*                                              │\n68: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n69:         │\n70:         ▼\n71: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n72: │ 2. AuthMiddleware                                               │\n73: │    - Extract Authorization header                               │\n74: │    - Validate \"Bearer \" prefix                                  │\n75: │    - Extract token string                                       │\n76: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n77:         │\n78:         ▼\n79: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n80: │ 3. JWT Token Parsing                                            │\n81: │    - jwt.Parse with RSA public key                              │\n82: │    - Validate signing method (RS256)                            │\n83: │    - Check expiration (required)                                │\n84: │    - Check issued-at (required)                                 │\n85: │    - Apply 1-minute leeway                                      │\n86: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n87:         │\n88:         ▼\n89: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n90: │ 4. Error Classification                                         │\n91: │    - jwt.ErrTokenExpired → 401 \"token is expired\"              │\n92: │    - jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid → 401 \"invalid signature\"    │\n93: │    - invalid signing method → 401 \"invalid signing method\"     │\n94: │    - other errors → 401 with error message                      │\n95: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n96:         │ (on success)\n97:         ▼\n98: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n99: │ 5. Request Body Limit                                           │\n100: │    - http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, 32MB)       │\n101: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n102:         │\n103:         ▼\n104: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n105: │ 6. Handler Execution                                            │\n106: │    - ExecuteHandler, UploadFileHandler, etc.                    │\n107: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Data Structures\n113: \n114: ### AuthManager (`auth.go`)\n115: \n116: ```go\n117: type AuthManager struct {\n118:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n119:     mutex     sync.RWMutex\n120: }\n121: \n122: const (\n123:     PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n124:     MaxBodySize     = 32 << 20  // 32 MB\n125: )\n126: ```\n127: \n128: ### Server (`server.go`)\n129: \n130: ```go\n131: type Server struct {\n132:     config      *Config\n133:     engine      *gin.Engine\n134:     httpServer  *http.Server\n135:     authManager *AuthManager\n136:     workspace   string\n137:     startTime   time.Time\n138: }\n139: \n140: const readHeaderTimeout = 10 * time.Second\n141: ```\n142: \n143: ### Config (`config.go`)\n144: \n145: ```go\n146: type Config struct {\n147:     Port      int\n148:     Workspace string\n149: }\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## API Contracts\n155: \n156: ### Endpoints Summary\n157: \n158: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler | Description |\n159: |----------|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n160: | `/health` | GET | None | `HealthCheckHandler` | Health check endpoint |\n161: | `/api/execute` | POST | JWT | `ExecuteHandler` | Execute code in sandbox |\n162: | `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file to sandbox |\n163: | `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List files in workspace |\n164: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file from sandbox |\n165: \n166: ### Request Headers\n167: \n168: | Header | Required | Format | Description |\n169: |--------|----------|--------|-------------|\n170: | `Authorization` | Yes (for /api/*) | `Bearer <token>` | JWT token from Router |\n171: | `Content-Type` | POST only | `application/json` | Request body format |\n172: \n173: ### JWT Token Structure\n174: \n175: ```json\n176: {\n177:   \"exp\": <unix timestamp + 5min>,\n178:   \"iat\": <unix timestamp>,\n179:   \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n180:   \"session_id\": \"<session ID>\",\n181:   \"sandbox_id\": \"<sandbox ID>\",\n182:   \"namespace\": \"<sandbox namespace>\",\n183:   \"name\": \"<sandbox name>\"\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Response Format\n188: \n189: **Success Response:**\n190: ```json\n191: {\n192:   \"status\": \"ok\",\n193:   \"data\": <response data>\n194: }\n195: ```\n196: \n197: **Error Response:**\n198: ```json\n199: {\n200:   \"error\": \"<error message>\"\n201: }\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Error Handling\n207: \n208: ### HTTP Status Codes\n209: \n210: | Status | Condition | Error Message |\n211: |--------|-----------|---------------|\n212: | 401 | Missing Authorization header | \"missing authorization header\" |\n213: | 401 | Invalid token format (no Bearer prefix) | \"invalid token format\" |\n214: | 401 | Token expired | \"token is expired\" |\n215: | 401 | Invalid signature | \"invalid signature\" |\n216: | 401 | Wrong signing method | \"invalid signing method\" |\n217: | 401 | Token invalid (other errors) | `<jwt library error message>` |\n218: | 401 | Token validation failed | \"invalid token\" |\n219: \n220: ### Error Response Examples\n221: \n222: ```json\n223: // Missing Authorization\n224: {\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}\n225: \n226: // Token Expired\n227: {\"error\": \"token is expired\"}\n228: \n229: // Invalid Signature\n230: {\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### Error Handling Strategy\n234: \n235: 1. **Header extraction**: Check Authorization header presence, reject with 401 if missing\n236: 2. **Format validation**: Ensure \"Bearer \" prefix exists, reject with 401 if invalid\n237: 3. **Token parsing**: Use `jwt.Parse` with RSA public key validation\n238: 4. **Expiration check**: Required (`jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`)\n239: 5. **Issued-at check**: Required (`jwt.WithIssuedAt()`)\n240: 6. **Clock skew**: 1-minute leeway (`jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`)\n241: 7. **Signing method**: Validate RS256, reject other methods\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## Testing Strategy\n246: \n247: ### Unit Tests\n248: \n249: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n250: |-----------|-------|----------|\n251: | `TestNewAuthManager` | Valid PEM public key in env | AuthManager created successfully |\n252: | `TestNewAuthManagerMissingKey` | No env variable | Error: \"public key environment variable not set\" |\n253: | `TestNewAuthManagerInvalidPEM` | Invalid PEM data | Error: \"failed to decode PEM block\" |\n254: | `TestNewAuthManagerWrongKeyType` | Non-RSA key | Error: \"public key is not RSA\" |\n255: | `TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnv` | Valid RSA PUBLIC KEY PEM | *rsa.PublicKey returned |\n256: | `TestAuthMiddlewareValidToken` | Valid JWT token | Request continues (200) |\n257: | `TestAuthMiddlewareMissingHeader` | No Authorization header | 401, \"missing authorization header\" |\n258: | `TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidFormat` | \"Basic token\" | 401, \"invalid token format\" |\n259: | `TestAuthMiddlewareExpiredToken` | Expired JWT | 401, \"token is expired\" |\n260: | `TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidSignature` | Token signed with different key | 401, \"invalid signature\" |\n261: | `TestAuthMiddlewareWrongSigningMethod` | HS256 signed token | 401, \"invalid signing method\" |\n262: | `TestAuthMiddlewareEmptyToken` | \"Bearer \" (empty) | 401, error message |\n263: | `TestSetGetPublicKey` | Set new public key | Get returns new key |\n264: | `TestPublicKeyConcurrency` | Concurrent Set/Get operations | Thread-safe access |\n265: \n266: ### Integration Tests\n267: \n268: | Scenario | Description |\n269: |----------|-------------|\n270: | Full request flow | Valid token → ExecuteHandler invoked |\n271: | Router-PicoD key sync | Token from Router validated by PicoD |\n272: | Key rotation | Update public key, new tokens work, old tokens fail |\n273: | Health endpoint bypass | /health accessible without token |\n274: \n275: ### Test Patterns\n276: \n277: ```go\n278: // Mock JWT token generation for testing\n279: func generateTestToken(claims map[string]interface{}, privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey) string {\n280:     token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, jwt.MapClaims(claims))\n281:     tokenString, _ := token.SignedString(privateKey)\n282:     return tokenString\n283: }\n284: \n285: // Setup test server with auth middleware\n286: func setupTestServer(authManager *AuthManager) *gin.Engine {\n287:     engine := gin.New()\n288:     engine.GET(\"/health\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n289:         c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n290:     })\n291:     api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n292:     api.Use(authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n293:     api.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n294:         c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"authenticated\"})\n295:     })\n296:     return engine\n297: }\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## File Structure\n303: \n304: ```\n305: pkg/picod/\n306: ├── auth.go            # AuthManager, JWT validation middleware\n307: ├── auth_test.go       # AuthManager unit tests\n308: ├── config.go          # Server configuration\n309: ├── doc.go             # Package documentation\n310: ├── execute.go         # Code execution handler\n311: ├── files.go           # File upload/download handlers\n312: ├── health.go          # Health check handler\n313: ├── picod_test.go      # Integration tests\n314: ├── sanitize.go        # Input sanitization utilities\n315: ├── server.go          # HTTP server setup and routing\n316: ```\n317: \n318: ---\n319: \n320: ## Dependencies\n321: \n322: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n323: |---------|---------|---------|\n324: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP router and middleware |\n325: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT parsing and validation |\n326: | `crypto/rsa` | stdlib | RSA public key handling |\n327: | `crypto/x509` | stdlib | PKIX public key parsing |\n328: | `encoding/pem` | stdlib | PEM encoding/decoding |\n329: | `sync` | stdlib | Thread-safe access |\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## Implementation Notes\n334: \n335: ### Key Loading\n336: \n337: ```go\n338: func LoadPublicKeyFromEnv() (*rsa.PublicKey, error) {\n339:     pemKey := strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar))\n340:     if pemKey == \"\" {\n341:         return nil, errors.New(\"public key environment variable not set\")\n342:     }\n343: \n344:     block, _ := pem.Decode([]byte(pemKey))\n345:     if block == nil {\n346:         return nil, errors.New(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n347:     }\n348: \n349:     if block.Type != \"PUBLIC KEY\" {\n350:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"expected PUBLIC KEY PEM block, got %s\", block.Type)\n351:     }\n352: \n353:     pub, err := x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)\n354:     if err != nil {\n355:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse public key: %w\", err)\n356:     }\n357: \n358:     rsaPub, ok := pub.(*rsa.PublicKey)\n359:     if !ok {\n360:         return nil, errors.New(\"public key is not RSA\")\n361:     }\n362: \n363:     return rsaPub, nil\n364: }\n365: ```\n366: \n367: ### JWT Validation Options\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: token, err := jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n371:     if _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n372:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid signing method\")\n373:     }\n374:     return pubKey, nil\n375: }, jwt.WithExpirationRequired(), jwt.WithIssuedAt(), jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Thread-Safe Key Updates\n379: \n380: ```go\n381: func (a *AuthManager) SetPublicKey(key *rsa.PublicKey) {\n382:     a.mutex.Lock()\n383:     a.publicKey = key\n384:     a.mutex.Unlock()\n385: }\n386: \n387: func (a *AuthManager) GetPublicKey() *rsa.PublicKey {\n388:     a.mutex.RLock()\n389:     defer a.mutex.RUnlock()\n390:     return a.publicKey\n391: }\n392: ```\n393: \n394: ### Request Body Size Limit\n395: \n396: ```go\n397: http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## References\n403: \n404: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` — JWTManager implementation (token generation)\n405: - `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` — Router JWT middleware (reference implementation)\n406: - `pkg/router/errors.go` — JWT error types (APIStatus interface)\n407: - `changes/AR-010/design.md` — Router session management design\n408: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client library reference\n409: - JWT library: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n\n(End of file - total 409 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPicoD JWT 中间件提供基于 RSA 公钥的 JWT token 验证机制，用于保护 PicoD 的 `/api/*` 端点。该中间件从环境变量加载公钥，验证请求中的 Bearer token，并将验证结果传递给后续处理器。\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775863638914,"end":1775863638936}}}}
