{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863731493,"sessionID":"ses_286479a04ffe1Yy62joY7hCNz1","part":{"id":"prt_d79ba14ca001RDi3mbkD5F7D0X","messageID":"msg_d79b8e505001IPFY6BhQ3ebb0d","sessionID":"ses_286479a04ffe1Yy62joY7hCNz1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9c0ee59c784c47a59f686b50cae24a59","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","content":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/auth.go` AuthManager struct exists\n  - Check: `AuthManager` struct with `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` and `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Struct compiles without error\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Verify `PublicKeyEnvVar` and `MaxBodySize` constants\n  - Check: `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n  - Check: `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20` (32 MB)\n  - Verify: `grep -n \"PublicKeyEnvVar\\|MaxBodySize\" pkg/picod/auth.go`\n  - Independently verifiable: Constants defined\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Verify `NewAuthManager` function exists\n  - Check: Function calls `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` and returns `*AuthManager`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n\n- [ ] **T1.4** Verify `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` function exists\n  - Check: Function reads env var, decodes PEM, parses PKIX public key, validates RSA type\n  - Check: Returns error for: missing env var, invalid PEM, wrong block type, non-RSA key\n  - Verify: `grep -n \"LoadPublicKeyFromEnv\" pkg/picod/auth.go`\n  - Independently verifiable: Function exists with proper error handling\n\n- [ ] **T1.5** Verify `AuthMiddleware` gin.HandlerFunc exists\n  - Check: Extracts Authorization header, validates \"Bearer \" prefix\n  - Check: Parses JWT with RS256 validation, expiration required, issued-at required, 1-minute leeway\n  - Check: Error classification: expired → \"token is expired\", invalid signature → \"invalid signature\"\n  - Check: Wrong signing method → \"invalid signing method\"\n  - Verify: `grep -n \"AuthMiddleware\" pkg/picod/auth.go`\n  - Independently verifiable: Middleware exists with proper error classification\n\n- [ ] **T1.6** Verify `SetPublicKey` and `GetPublicKey` methods exist\n  - Check: Thread-safe key update and retrieval with mutex\n  - Verify: `grep -n \"SetPublicKey\\|GetPublicKey\" pkg/picod/auth.go`\n  - Independently verifiable: Methods exist with proper locking\n\n- [ ] **T1.7** Verify auth middleware integration in `pkg/picod/server.go`\n  - Check: `/api/*` routes use `authManager.AuthMiddleware()`\n  - Check: `/health` route bypasses auth middleware\n  - Verify: `grep -n \"AuthMiddleware\\|/health\\|/api\" pkg/picod/server.go`\n  - Independently verifiable: Routes properly configured\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: AuthManager Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Test `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` missing env var\n  - Test: `TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvMissing` exists and passes\n  - Expected: Error \"public key environment variable not set\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvMissing ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Test `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` invalid PEM\n  - Test: `TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvInvalidPEM` exists and passes\n  - Expected: Error \"failed to decode PEM block\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvInvalidPEM ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Test `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` PKCS1 format rejection\n  - Test: `TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvPKCS1Format` exists and passes\n  - Expected: Error \"expected PUBLIC KEY PEM block\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvPKCS1Format ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Test `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` valid key\n  - Test: `TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvValid` exists and passes\n  - Expected: Returns valid `*rsa.PublicKey`\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnvValid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Add test for `NewAuthManager` with valid key\n  - Create: `TestNewAuthManagerValid`\n  - Setup: Set valid PEM public key in env var\n  - Expected: AuthManager created successfully\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestNewAuthManagerValid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.6** Add test for `NewAuthManager` with missing key\n  - Create: `TestNewAuthManagerMissingKey`\n  - Setup: Unset env var\n  - Expected: Error \"failed to load public key: public key environment variable not set\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestNewAuthManagerMissingKey ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.7** Add test for `NewAuthManager` with invalid PEM\n  - Create: `TestNewAuthManagerInvalidPEM`\n  - Setup: Set invalid PEM data in env var\n  - Expected: Error contains \"failed to decode PEM block\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestNewAuthManagerInvalidPEM ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.8** Add test for `NewAuthManager` with wrong key type\n  - Create: `TestNewAuthManagerWrongKeyType`\n  - Setup: Create ECDSA key, encode as PEM PUBLIC KEY\n  - Expected: Error \"public key is not RSA\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestNewAuthManagerWrongKeyType ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: AuthMiddleware Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Test missing Authorization header\n  - Test: `TestAuthMiddlewareMissingHeader` exists and passes\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, {\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareMissingHeader ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Test invalid token format (no Bearer prefix)\n  - Test: `TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidFormat` exists and passes\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, error contains \"malformed\" or \"invalid token format\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidFormat ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Test expired token\n  - Test: `TestAuthMiddlewareExpiredToken` exists and passes\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, {\"error\": \"token is expired\"}\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareExpiredToken ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Test HS256 signed token (wrong signing method)\n  - Test: `TestAuthMiddlewareHS256Token` exists and passes\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, {\"error\": \"invalid signing method\"}\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareHS256Token ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Test valid RS256 token\n  - Test: `TestAuthMiddlewareValidRS256Token` exists and passes\n  - Expected: HTTP 200, request continues to handler\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareValidRS256Token ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.6** Add test for invalid signature (token signed with different key)\n  - Create: `TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidSignature`\n  - Setup: Generate two RSA key pairs; sign with one, validate with another\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, {\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidSignature ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.7** Add test for empty token (\"Bearer \" with no token)\n  - Create: `TestAuthMiddlewareEmptyToken`\n  - Setup: Authorization header = \"Bearer \"\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, error returned\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareEmptyToken ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T3.8** Add test for health endpoint bypass (no auth required)\n  - Test: `TestHealthCheckHandler` exists and passes\n  - Expected: HTTP 200 without Authorization header\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestHealthCheckHandler ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: Thread-Safety Tests\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Add test for `SetPublicKey` and `GetPublicKey`\n  - Create: `TestSetGetPublicKey`\n  - Steps: Create AuthManager, SetPublicKey, GetPublicKey, verify returned key matches\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestSetGetPublicKey ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Add test for concurrent Set/Get operations\n  - Create: `TestPublicKeyConcurrency`\n  - Steps: Multiple goroutines calling SetPublicKey and GetPublicKey concurrently\n  - Expected: Thread-safe access, no race conditions\n  - Verify: `go test -race -run TestPublicKeyConcurrency ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes with race detector\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Test full request flow with valid token\n  - Test: `TestExecuteHandlerValidCommand` exists and passes\n  - Setup: Valid JWT token, POST /api/execute\n  - Expected: HTTP 200, handler invoked, execute response returned\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestExecuteHandlerValidCommand ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Add test for key rotation\n  - Create: `TestAuthMiddlewareKeyRotation`\n  - Steps: Generate key1, create token1; set key1 to AuthManager; validate token1 succeeds\n  - Steps: Generate key2, set key2 to AuthManager; validate token2 succeeds; validate token1 fails\n  - Expected: After rotation, old tokens fail, new tokens succeed\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestAuthMiddlewareKeyRotation ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Validation and Linting\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Run `go vet` on picod package\n  - Run: `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n  - Verify: No warnings\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Run `golangci-lint` on picod package\n  - Run: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n  - Verify: No errors\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Run all tests with race detector\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n  - Verify: All tests pass\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n  - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n  - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n\n---\n\n### Phase 7: Binary Validation\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Build picod binary\n  - Run: `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod/`\n  - Verify: Binary exists\n  - Independently verifiable: `ls picod`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Run binary with test public key\n  - Setup: Generate RSA key pair, set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n  - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n  - Call: `/health` endpoint\n  - Expected: HTTP 200 response\n  - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Test JWT authentication via binary\n  - Setup: Server running with valid public key, generate JWT with matching private key\n  - Call: `POST /api/execute` with valid JWT\n  - Expected: HTTP 200, execute response\n  - Independently verifiable: Authenticated request succeeds\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Test JWT rejection via binary\n  - Setup: Server running, send request without Authorization header\n  - Call: `POST /api/execute`\n  - Expected: HTTP 401, {\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}\n  - Independently verifiable: Unauthenticated request rejected\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/auth.go` contains AuthManager struct with publicKey and mutex\n- [ ] `PublicKeyEnvVar` and `MaxBodySize` constants defined\n- [ ] `NewAuthManager` creates AuthManager from env var public key\n- [ ] `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` validates PEM format, PKIX parsing, RSA type\n- [ ] `AuthMiddleware` validates Bearer token format, JWT parsing, RS256 signing method\n- [ ] `AuthMiddleware` classifies errors: expired, invalid signature, wrong signing method\n- [ ] `SetPublicKey` and `GetPublicKey` provide thread-safe key access\n- [ ] `/api/*` routes protected by AuthMiddleware\n- [ ] `/health` route bypasses auth middleware\n- [ ] All auth middleware tests pass\n- [ ] Thread-safety tests pass with race detector\n- [ ] Pass `go vet`\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n- [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and protects API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines Changed |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `pkg/picod/auth.go` | Existing | ~130 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/server.go` | Existing | Auth middleware at line 68 |\n| `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Modify | +~30 lines (new tests) |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Existing | ~35 lines |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Public key loaded from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- PEM block type must be \"PUBLIC KEY\" (PKIX format, not PKCS1)\n- JWT validation options: `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n- Signing method must be RSA (RS256), other methods rejected with \"invalid signing method\"\n- Thread-safe key updates via mutex for potential key rotation scenarios\n- Request body size limit: 32 MB applied after successful auth\n- Health endpoint (`/health`) bypasses auth middleware for monitoring"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/auth.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":87,"character":63},"end":{"line":87,"character":74}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by 